Two games, two managers, two defeats, two goals conceded to Kenwyne Jones. The Championship has not been terribly kind to Huddersfield Town in the first steps of this season.

It’s been a strange old week for the Terriers, who seem to have lost a little of their yap, not to mention Mark Robins.

Mark Lillis, the club’s caretaker for a third time in three years, probably put it best when he said ‘losing a manager after one game is a new one for me’.

