‘He came to us in January having played not much football,’ Solskjaer said. ‘He played a couple of games on adrenaline and the fitness caught up with him. It is an important season for him.’

The same can be said of Solskjaer. For Huddersfield, the ambitions are lower but no less intense.

‘It’s our third season in the Championship and we want to stay there,’ said Lillis. Things will have to improve under their third manager of the season.

 

